"This is not a spy story or mystery where the plot hinges around sophisticated eavesdropping devices. In this case, the computer played a minor part while the starring role went to the sorts of behavioural antics we have witnessed on a number of occasions in recent years. Thinking like a blackhat may be the best way to stop them from attacking your network. How can security staff take a blackhat-like view of their networks to seal off the holes before others exploit them?"
